<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🧊 M003 Extension 2 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> 3D Mob Heads (x, y, z) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Extension (after Week 3) · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>Build <strong>two mob heads</strong> in 3D — a <strong>creeper</strong> and a <strong>piglin</strong>. Now every block needs <strong>three</strong> numbers: <strong>(x, y, z)</strong>. x is <strong>across</strong>, y is <strong>up</strong>, z is <strong>forward</strong> (depth). Both heads stand in front of you in the world — walk around them, then copy one block by block.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move your feet, move your head.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each set. Write what you will see.</p>
<pre><code>place green block at (3, 5, 1)
place green block at (3, 5, 2)
place green block at (3, 5, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only z changes. Does the line go across, up, or deeper?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place green block at (4, 5, 1)
place green block at (4, 6, 1)
place green block at (4, 7, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Only y changes. Across, up, or deeper?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place green block at (3, 5, 1)
place black block at (3, 5, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Same (x, y, z). Green, black, or both? Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>Fix each one. Then say why it was wrong.</p>
<p><strong>Bug A</strong> — This block should sit one step <strong>deeper</strong>, at (3, 5, 2). It only has two numbers, so it lands on the front.</p>
<pre><code>place green block at (3, 5)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — The eye should be <strong>up high and one step deep</strong>: (4, 7, 2). The last two numbers are swapped.</p>
<pre><code>place black block at (4, 2, 7)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — Code is correct, but the whole head came out one step too far forward.</p>
<pre><code>(the code matched the head)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What did your friend forget before pressing run?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Build a Head 🧱</h2>
<p>Pick <strong>one</strong> head in the world. Walk around it. Then build your own on your home spot.</p>
<p><strong>Start with the front face</strong> (keep z the same, e.g. z = 1). Read each block's <strong>x</strong> (across) and <strong>y</strong> (up).</p>
<p><strong>Then add depth.</strong> Build the same face again at z = 2, then z = 3, until your head is as deep as the real one.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>💡 Tip: the eyes and mouth only show on the <strong>front</strong>. The sides and back are plain.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Send a photo. Then finish these — 4 to 6 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I built the …</p>
<p>The lowest front block is at (x = …, y = …, z = …).</p>
<p>To go up I changed the … number; to go deeper I changed the … number.</p>
<p>My head is … blocks deep.</p>
<p>Once my head was wrong because …</p>
<p>Next time I would …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Film yourself showing your head. Use these words: <strong>x</strong>, <strong>y</strong>, <strong>z</strong>, <strong>across</strong>, <strong>up</strong>, <strong>forward</strong>, <strong>home spot</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your home spot. Why stand on it every time?</li>
<li>Walk around your head — show the front, a side, and the back.</li>
<li>Point at one block: "this one is at x …, y …, z …".</li>
<li>Show one block you fixed.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Plan what you will say:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your video on KakaoTalk.</p>
